headline: General Motors (GM) Is Up 7.1% After Q3 Delivery Jump and Supply Chain Shift Plans
summary: General Motors recently reported an 8% year-over-year increase in Q3 vehicle deliveries, raised its full-year outlook, and outlined plans to shift supplier sourcing away from China by 2027 to boost supply chain resilience and secure eligibility for U.S. tax credits. GM’s fleet and commercial business saw OnStar subscriptions surge over 50% to 1.6 million, underscoring the growing potential of digital services as a higher-margin revenue stream.
